06/08/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- President Ahmet Necdet Sezer on Monday (August 6th) formally asked Justice and Development Party (AKP) leader Recep Tayyip Erdogan to form a new government. 
"Drawing on our experience of four years and eight months in government, we will hopefully form a stronger government that will overcome many shortcomings," Erdogan told reporters after meeting with Sezer. 
By law he has 45 days to assemble his cabinet. 
The AKP won a landslide victory in the July 22nd general elections.
In other news, Turkey assumes rotating command of the Black Sea Naval Co-operation Task Group (Blackseafor) from Russia on Monday. 
The term last for a year. 
Other members include Bulgaria, Georgia, and Ukraine. 
(Zaman, Anadolu Agency, Focus, CNN Turk - 06/08/07)
